<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-06-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="216" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">No. 216.</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Becerra</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-06-20"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 20,
                                1885</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Acknowledging the receipt of your note of
                            the 18th instant, I have the honor to say that its statements concerning
                            your regret for the delayed action of the Colombian consul at New York,
                            in the matter of the brig Ambrose Light, have been made known to the
                            Attorney-General.</p>
                        <p>Accept, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>T. F. BAYARD.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>